div.style: color: rgb(74, 20, 140) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

P(both fail) = P(A)P(B) + rhosqrt[P(A)*(1-P(A))P(B)(1-P(B))]
Where rho is phi correlation between binary 0/1 failure indicators
NOT conditional probability P(B|A), but correlation of failure events
